    "body": "Hey @aster2709, the problem here is that you have a `development` and `test` network defined in your `truffle-config.js`. If you have a configuration there with either of those names, it will assume you want to connect to a network at one of those configurations (I think it will default to `development` over `test`) and attempt to connect. Since you haven't started a network there it will give you the message you are reporting here and error. If Truffle doesn't find a configuration with one of those two names it will spin up its own instance of Ganache under the hood. So this is actually intended behavior. ",
