    "body": "@aster2709 you do have to run ganache in a separate tab (`ganache-cli`, or specify the port with `ganache-cli -p 7545`). Have you done that? If you want a ganache instance spun up for you, then try running `truffle develop` to spin up a REPL, and in there you can run all of your commands without the `truffle` prefix -- so just `test`, `migrate`, `compile`, etc. \r\n\r\nI hope that helps!",
